Input.name: First Sudanese Civil War
Answer.Ans1: The country that began to be a belligerent in the First Sudanese Civil War the same year the Democratic Republic of the Sudan stopped its involvement was Israel, starting in 1969.
Answer.Res1: The reason behind Israel's involvement in the conflict was primarily driven by its strategic interests in the region. During the late 1960s, Sudan was seen as a potential threat to Israel due to its close ties with Arab countries and its support for Palestinian militant groups. Sudan's President at the time, Gaafar Nimeiry, had aligned the country with Arab nationalist movements and openly criticized Israel.

Years of Lead (Italy)
Part of the Cold War

Aftermath of the bombing at the Bologna railway station in August 1980 which killed 85 people, the deadliest event during the Years of Lead
DateLate 1968 – mid 1988 (20 years)
Resurgence from 1999 – 2005 (6 years)
Location
Italy (mainly Northern Italy)
Result

Eventual decrease of terrorist activity in Italy:

  • The murder of Aldo Moro (1978) resulted in a collapse of popular support for the Red Brigades
  • The Bologna massacre (1980) led to the dismantling of the main far-right terrorist groups
  • The Propaganda Due affair (1981) caused the decline of secret circles for several years
